defaultSince 1970 UK mineral production has been dominated by
default energy minerals, initially coal, but later oil and gas following the development of 
defaultlarge 
defaultof
defaultfshore reserves from the 1970s. The 
defaultvalue of coal production 
defaulthas declined in line with 
defaultsteadily 
defaultfalling output since the mid-1980
defaults
default. 
default 
defaultThe 
defaultrapidly 
defaultrising value of oil production up to 1984 was reversed by t
defaulthe slump in world 
defaultoil 
defaultprices at the end of 1985, and
default again in 1988, and also the loss of production through the Piper Alpha tragedy
default.
default Following rising oil prices since 2000, however, the value of UK oil productions has risen and was still £25.5 billion in 2011
default.
default Despite falling oil and gas production since 2000, the value of both have held up well because of high prices.  Ultimately, however, as reserves are depleted their value will decline.
